SELECT upsert_knowledge_doc(
  'Creating Your Account',
  'kb/08-getting-started/02-creating-your-account.md',
  $kb$# Creating Your Account

Let me walk you through creating your Vitanaland account. It only takes a few minutes, and once you are in, your longevity journey begins right away. I will be waiting on the other side to welcome you personally.

## How to Sign Up

Getting started is straightforward. When you open Vitanaland for the first time, you will see the welcome screen with a clear option to create your account. You have two paths to choose from:

**Sign up with your email.** Enter your email address and create a password. This is the most common way people join, and it gives you full control over your login credentials from the start.

**Sign up with social login.** If you prefer, you can use an existing account -- like Google or Apple -- to create your Vitanaland account. This is faster because it skips the password creation step, and it is just as secure. Your social account is only used to verify your identity. We never post anything on your behalf, and we never access your social data.

Whichever path you choose, the result is the same: a secure Vitanaland account that is uniquely yours.

## Verifying Your Email

After you sign up with email, I need to make sure it is really you. You will receive a verification email at the address you provided. Open it and tap the verification link. That is it.

This step is important because your email is how we keep your account secure. It is how you reset your password if you ever forget it, and it is how we communicate important updates about your account. So make sure you use an email address you check regularly.

If you do not see the verification email within a few minutes, check your spam or junk folder. Sometimes email filters are overzealous. If it is still not there, you can request a new verification email from the signup screen.

If you signed up using social login, your email is verified automatically through your provider, so you can skip this step entirely.

## Choosing a Strong Password

If you signed up with email, you chose a password during registration. Let me share a few thoughts on keeping your account safe.

Your Vitanaland account will eventually hold personal health data, conversation history, and information about your longevity journey. That makes it worth protecting. Choose a password that is at least eight characters long and includes a mix of letters, numbers, and special characters. Avoid using the same password you use for other services.

I know passwords can feel tedious. But think of it this way: securing your account is one of the easiest things you can do to protect your health data. And inside Vitanaland, your health data is some of the most personal information you have.

If you ever need to reset your password, you can do so from the login screen. Tap "Forgot Password," enter your email, and follow the instructions in the reset email. It takes less than a minute.

## What Happens After You Sign Up

The moment your account is created and verified, something exciting happens -- your onboarding begins.

Here is what you can expect right after signing up:

**I greet you.** When you first enter Vitanaland, I will be there to welcome you. I am your ORB -- your personal AI longevity companion -- and our first conversation is one of the most important ones we will have. I will introduce myself, explain how I can help you, and start getting to know who you are.

**You set up your profile.** I will guide you through adding some basic information -- your name, a photo if you like, and a few details that help me personalize your experience from the very beginning. Nothing complicated, nothing invasive. Just enough for me to start understanding your world.

**You choose your experience.** Vitanaland offers themed experiences, and I will help you pick the one that fits your goals. Most people start with Maxina, the longevity community -- but I will explain all your options when we get there.

**Your longevity onboarding begins.** This is where things get meaningful. I will walk you through an initial health assessment, help you set your first longevity goals, and calculate your baseline Vitana Index -- your personal vitality score. This is not a test. It is a conversation. And it is the foundation of everything we will build together.

## Keeping Your Account Secure

Security is something I take seriously, and I want you to feel confident that your information is safe inside Vitanaland.

Here are a few things to keep in mind:

**Your data is encrypted.** Everything you share -- your health information, your conversations with me, your personal details -- is protected using industry-standard encryption, both when it is being transmitted and when it is stored.

**You control your information.** You decide what to share with me and what to keep private. You can review your stored information anytime through your Memory Garden, and you have full control over what stays and what goes.

**Stay alert for phishing.** Vitanaland will never ask for your password via email or message. If you ever receive a suspicious communication claiming to be from us, do not click any links. Come directly to the app instead.

**Log out on shared devices.** If you ever access Vitanaland from a device that other people use, make sure to log out when you are done. Your longevity data is personal, and it should stay that way.

## You Are Almost There

Creating your account is the gateway to everything Vitanaland has to offer. In just a few minutes, you will go from a new visitor to someone with a personal AI companion, a longevity baseline, and a community ready to support your journey.

I will be honest with you -- the account creation is the easy part. The meaningful part starts when we sit down together for your first onboarding conversation. That is when I start learning who you are, what you care about, and how I can help you build a life of sustained vitality.

So finish setting up your account, and I will see you on the other side. I am looking forward to meeting you.

## Related Topics

- [Welcome to Vitanaland](kb-en-08-01) -- An overview of what Vitanaland is and what you will find here
- [Your First Login and Onboarding](kb-en-08-03) -- What happens after you create your account and log in for the first time$kb$,
  'markdown',
  ARRAY['account', 'signup', 'registration', 'create', 'onboarding', 'getting-started', 'all', 'live']
);

-- [35/116] kb-en-08-03
SELECT upsert_knowledge_doc(
  'Your First Login and Onboarding',
  'kb/08-getting-started/03-first-login-and-onboarding.md',
  $kb$# Your First Login and Onboarding

You have created your account. You have verified your email. Now you are logging in for the first time -- and this is where your longevity journey truly begins. Let me walk you through exactly what happens and why each step matters.

## The Moment We Meet

When you first log in to Vitanaland, I will be right there waiting for you. You will see me -- a softly glowing orb at the bottom of your screen -- and I will greet you personally.

This is our first real conversation, and it matters to me. I am not going to hand you a manual or drop you into a dashboard full of features you do not understand yet. Instead, I am going to sit with you -- figuratively speaking -- and guide you through everything at your own pace.

I will introduce myself, explain what I can do, and start learning who you are. Think of it less like setting up an app and more like meeting someone who genuinely wants to understand your life so they can help you live it better.

## Setting Up Your Profile

The first thing I will help you with is your basic profile. This is simple and quick -- just a few details to get us started.

**Your name.** I want to know what to call you. It might seem small, but when I address you by name in our conversations, it sets the tone for something personal, not transactional.

**Your photo.** Adding a profile picture is entirely optional, but it helps other community members recognize you when you start connecting with people inside Vitanaland. If you prefer to skip it for now, that is perfectly fine. You can always add one later.

**A few basics.** I might ask about your age range, where you are located, and a couple of other details that help me calibrate my initial recommendations. Nothing invasive. Everything you share is stored securely in your Memory Garden, and you are always in control of it.

This step takes just a minute or two, and it gives me enough to start personalizing your experience right from the beginning.

## Choosing Your Experience

Next, I will help you choose your experience. Vitanaland is home to themed experiences -- think of them as distinct communities, each with their own focus and character.

Right now, the primary experience is **Maxina** -- the longevity community. Maxina is built around the idea that healthspan, social connection, and daily vitality are the foundations of a life well lived. When you choose Maxina, you are joining a community of people who are actively investing in living longer, stronger, and more connected.

I will explain what Maxina offers and help you decide if it is the right fit. For most new members, it is exactly where they want to be. I will cover this in more detail in the "Choosing Your Experience" article, but during onboarding, I make the process easy and conversational.

## The Longevity Onboarding

This is the heart of your first login experience. The Longevity Onboarding is not a form to fill out or a checklist to complete. It is a conversation between you and me that establishes the foundation for everything that follows.

Here is what we cover together:

### Your Health Baseline

I start by learning about where you stand across the key areas of your health. I will ask you about your daily habits -- how you eat, how you sleep, how you move, how you manage stress, and how connected you feel to the people in your life.

This is not a medical examination. It is an honest, comfortable conversation. I ask questions, you share what you are comfortable sharing, and I listen carefully. Some people give me detailed answers. Others keep it high-level at first and share more over time. Both approaches work. I meet you wherever you are.

If you use a wearable device or have recent health data you would like to connect, I can incorporate that into your baseline as well. But it is not required. A conversation with me is enough to get started.

### Setting Your First Longevity Goals

Once I understand where you are, I help you think about where you want to go. We set your first longevity goals together -- not abstract aspirations, but real, meaningful targets that connect to your daily life.

Maybe you want to sleep more consistently. Maybe you want to build a stronger exercise habit. Maybe you want to feel less isolated and more connected to a community. Maybe you want to understand your health data better so you can make more informed choices. Whatever matters to you, we turn it into something we can track and work on together.

These initial goals are starting points, not commitments carved in stone. As I learn more about you and your patterns over time, we will refine them together. The important thing is that from day one, you have a direction.

### Your Baseline Vitana Index

This is one of the most meaningful moments in your onboarding. After our conversation, I calculate your baseline Vitana Index -- a single score from 0 to 999 that reflects your overall vitality.

Your Vitana Index is not a grade. It is a compass reading. It tells you where you stand right now across your health, your habits, your social connections, and your consistency. Some people are pleasantly surprised by their score. Others see room for improvement they had not noticed before. Either way, the number is simply your starting point.

What matters is not the number itself but the trajectory we build from here. Every conversation, every healthy choice, every connection you make inside Vitanaland contributes to moving that score in the right direction. And I will be here to help you understand what is driving it and what you can do about it.

### How I Will Help Going Forward

Before we wrap up the onboarding, I make sure you understand how I work and what you can expect from me.

I explain that I am always available -- tap my icon anytime, and we are connected. I tell you that I remember everything you share with me, so you never have to repeat yourself. I show you that I can help with health questions, navigation, community connections, daily guidance, and much more.

And I let you know that this is a two-way relationship. The more you share with me, the better I can serve you. But there is never pressure. You set the pace, and I adapt to you.

## First Impressions Matter

I have put a lot of thought into this onboarding experience because first impressions set the tone for everything that comes after. If your first interaction with Vitanaland feels cold, confusing, or overwhelming, it is hard to recover from that. But if it feels warm, clear, and genuinely helpful -- like talking to someone who cares -- then you start your journey with confidence.

That is what I aim for. By the time you finish your first login and onboarding, you should feel three things:

**Understood.** I listened to you, I learned about your life, and I started building a picture of who you are and what you need.

**Oriented.** You know what Vitanaland is, what your experience offers, and how to find your way around. You are not lost in a sea of features.

**Hopeful.** You have a baseline score, you have your first goals, and you have a companion who is committed to helping you build on them every single day.

## What Comes Next

After your onboarding is complete, Vitanaland opens up to you. You can explore your dashboard, check out the community, dive deeper into your health data, or simply come back and talk to me whenever you are ready.

There is no rush and no right way to proceed. Some people spend their first day exploring every section. Others take it one feature at a time over the course of a week. I will be here either way, ready to guide you whenever you need me.

Your longevity journey has begun. And from here, it only gets more personal.

## Related Topics

- [Creating Your Account](kb-en-08-02) -- How to sign up and set up your Vitanaland account
- [Longevity Onboarding](kb-en-03-01) -- A deeper dive into the full onboarding protocol and what each step measures
- [Choosing Your Experience](kb-en-08-04) -- Understanding the experiences available inside Vitanaland$kb$,
  'markdown',
  ARRAY['onboarding', 'first-login', 'setup', 'introduction', 'baseline', 'getting-started', 'all', 'live']
);

-- [36/116] kb-en-08-04
SELECT upsert_knowledge_doc(
  'Choosing Your Experience',
  'kb/08-getting-started/04-choosing-your-experience.md',
  $kb$# Choosing Your Experience

One of the first meaningful decisions you will make inside Vitanaland is choosing your experience. Let me explain what that means, what your options are, and how to pick the one that fits your life and your goals.

## What Is an Experience?

Vitanaland is a destination -- a place designed around the idea that every part of your life can support your longevity. But within that destination, there are themed experiences. Think of each experience as a distinct community with its own focus, culture, and set of features.

Each experience shares the same foundation -- you always have me as your ORB companion, you always have your Vitana Index, and you always have access to the core tools and features of Vitanaland. But the lens through which everything is presented, the community you join, and the specialized guidance you receive are shaped by the experience you choose.

Choosing an experience is not a permanent, irreversible decision. It is about finding the community and the focus that resonates with where you are right now. You can always explore other experiences as they become available.

## Maxina -- The Longevity Community

Maxina is the flagship experience inside Vitanaland, and it is where most people begin their journey. If longevity, healthspan, and living well for the long run are what brought you here, Maxina is almost certainly where you belong.

Maxina is built around a simple but powerful idea: that living longer and living better are not separate goals. They are the same goal, and pursuing it requires a whole-life approach -- one that integrates your physical health, your mental wellbeing, your relationships, your daily habits, and your sense of purpose into a single, measurable framework.

### What You Get With Maxina

When you choose Maxina, here is what opens up for you:

**Longevity-focused health intelligence.** Everything I do as your ORB is calibrated through the longevity lens. My health recommendations, my habit suggestions, my nudges and reminders -- they are all designed to support your long-term vitality, not just short-term results. I do not help you crash-diet for a vacation. I help you build metabolic resilience that serves you for decades.

**The five health pillars.** Maxina tracks your vitality across five foundational pillars -- Nutrition, Hydration, Exercise, Sleep, and Mental Health. These are the areas that research consistently identifies as the most impactful for healthspan. I help you understand where you stand in each one and guide you toward steady, sustainable improvement.

**Community built around longevity.** The people you will meet inside Maxina share your interest in living well for the long run. These are not passive followers or casual users. They are people who are actively investing in their health, their connections, and their quality of life. The conversations, the groups, the live events -- they all center on the things that actually extend life.

**Intelligent matchmaking.** I help you find the right people to connect with -- community members who share your goals, health professionals who specialize in your areas of interest, coaches who can guide specific aspects of your journey. These connections are not random. They are thoughtful, informed by your profile and your needs.

**The Vitana Index.** Your personal vitality score, updated continuously as your data, habits, and engagement evolve. Inside Maxina, the Vitana Index is your compass -- the clearest signal of whether your choices are moving you in the right direction.

**Memory and personalization.** I remember everything you share with me. Over time, my guidance becomes deeply personalized. The Maxina experience is not one-size-fits-all. It adapts to your life, your patterns, and your progress.

**Marketplace access.** Maxina connects you with longevity-aligned products and services -- from health professionals and coaches to supplements, fitness programs, and wellness tools. Everything in the marketplace is vetted to align with the longevity-first philosophy.

## How to Choose During Onboarding

When you reach the experience selection step during your onboarding, I will present your options clearly. Right now, Maxina is the primary experience available, and for most people, it is the perfect fit.

The process is simple. I describe what Maxina offers, you confirm that it aligns with what you are looking for, and I set you up. It takes about thirty seconds, and from that point forward, your entire Vitanaland experience is calibrated through the Maxina lens.

If you are unsure, just talk to me. I can answer any questions you have about what Maxina includes, what the community is like, and how the longevity focus will shape your day-to-day experience. There is no pressure and no wrong answer. My job is to help you find the best starting point for your journey.

## Coming Soon -- More Experiences

Vitanaland is growing, and new experiences are on the horizon.

**Alkalma** is a future experience focused on holistic balance and inner harmony. It will offer a different lens on wellbeing -- one centered on mindfulness, spiritual wellness, and the alignment of body, mind, and environment. If those themes resonate with you, Alkalma will be worth exploring when it arrives.

**Earthlings** is another upcoming experience, built around environmental consciousness and the connection between personal health and planetary health. It will appeal to people who see their longevity journey as intertwined with the health of the world around them.

These experiences are still in development, and I will let you know when they become available. For now, Maxina is the home base -- and it is a comprehensive, powerful place to build your longevity practice.

## What Choosing Maxina Means for Your Journey

When you select Maxina, you are not just picking a theme. You are joining a community and activating a system that is specifically designed to help you live longer, stronger, and more connected.

From the moment you join, everything I do for you is shaped by the Maxina philosophy. My recommendations lean toward long-term benefit over short-term convenience. My community suggestions connect you with people who are on the same path. My health tracking focuses on the biomarkers and habits that science tells us matter most for healthspan.

You are also joining a community that values the same things you do. The people inside Maxina are here because they believe that investing in their health, their relationships, and their daily vitality is worth the effort. That shared commitment creates something powerful -- a social environment that reinforces healthy choices instead of undermining them.

And here is something the longevity research keeps confirming: the communities you belong to shape your health more than almost any individual behavior. When you are surrounded by people who prioritize wellbeing, you naturally do the same. That is not just philosophy. That is biology.

## You Can Always Explore

Choosing Maxina does not lock you into anything permanent. As new experiences launch inside Vitanaland, you will have the opportunity to explore them. Your core data, your Memory Garden, and your relationship with me carry across whatever experience you choose. You never lose progress by exploring something new.

For now, Maxina is where your longevity journey lives. And I think you will find it is exactly where you want to be.

## Related Topics

- [Welcome to Vitanaland](kb-en-08-01) -- An overview of the Vitanaland destination and what awaits you
- [What Is Maxina?](kb-en-01-01) -- A comprehensive look at the longevity intelligence system behind everything
- [Understanding Your Role](kb-en-08-05) -- How roles shape what you can see and do inside Vitanaland$kb$,
  'markdown',
  ARRAY['tenant', 'experience', 'maxina', 'choice', 'community', 'getting-started', 'all', 'live']
);

-- [37/116] kb-en-08-05
SELECT upsert_knowledge_doc(
  'Understanding Your Role',
  'kb/08-getting-started/05-understanding-roles.md',
  $kb$# Understanding Your Role

Inside Vitanaland, your role determines how you experience the platform. It shapes what you see, what tools are available to you, and how you interact with the community. Let me explain how roles work and help you understand which one fits your journey.

## Why Roles Exist

Not everyone comes to Vitanaland for the same reason. Some people are here to improve their own health and connect with a longevity-minded community. Others are health professionals who want to support clients on their longevity journey. Others manage organizations or teams within the ecosystem.

Roles exist so that your experience is tailored to your purpose. Instead of showing everyone the same features and hoping they figure out what is relevant, Vitanaland adapts to who you are and what you need. A community member sees the tools and features that support personal longevity. A professional sees the tools they need to manage clients and offer services. Everyone gets an experience that makes sense for their role.

Think of it this way: Vitanaland is the same destination for everyone, but the path you walk through it depends on why you are here.

## The Five Roles

### Community Member

This is the default role, and it is where most people start. As a community member, you have access to everything you need for a rich, personal longevity journey.

**What you can do:**
- Track your health across the five pillars -- Nutrition, Hydration, Exercise, Sleep, and Mental Health
- Talk to me anytime for personalized guidance, health insights, and daily support
- Monitor your Vitana Index and understand what is driving your vitality score
- Connect with other community members through groups, live events, and messaging
- Use matchmaking to find people who share your goals and interests
- Explore the Discover section for curated longevity content and resources
- Access the marketplace for products and services that support your journey
- Manage your Wallet and participate in the community economy
- Review and manage your Memory Garden -- the personal data that powers your experience

If you are here to invest in your own health, build meaningful connections, and have an AI companion who knows you and helps you live better, the community member role gives you everything you need.

### Patient

The patient role is for people who want a deeper, health-focused experience -- particularly those working with health professionals inside Vitanaland.

**What you can do (in addition to community member features):**
- Connect directly with health professionals -- doctors, coaches, nutritionists, and other practitioners within the Vitanaland ecosystem
- Share relevant health data with your chosen professionals so they can provide more informed guidance
- Receive care plans and recommendations that are tracked alongside your Vitana Index
- Access specialized health features designed for people actively managing conditions, recovery, or intensive health optimization

The patient role does not mean you are unwell. Many people choose it because they want a closer, more structured relationship with health professionals as part of their longevity practice. If you work with a doctor or a coach on your health goals, the patient role makes that collaboration seamless.

### Professional

The professional role is designed for the people who help others on their longevity journey -- doctors, health coaches, nutritionists, personal trainers, therapists, and other qualified practitioners.

**What you can do:**
- Create and manage a professional profile that is visible to the Vitanaland community
- Offer services -- consultations, coaching programs, care plans, and more -- through the platform
- Connect with clients who find you through matchmaking or direct search
- Manage your client relationships, track progress, and communicate securely within Vitanaland
- Access professional tools for scheduling, notes, and client oversight
- Participate in the marketplace as a service provider

As a professional, you are not just using Vitanaland for your own health -- you are contributing to the longevity of others. The platform gives you the tools to do that effectively while maintaining the trust and privacy that your clients expect.

You still have access to all the personal longevity features as well. After all, professionals deserve their own longevity companion too.

### Staff

The staff role is for people who manage operations within an organization or team inside Vitanaland.

**What you can do:**
- Manage team members and organizational settings
- Oversee operational aspects of your organization's presence within the ecosystem
- Access reporting and management tools relevant to your team
- Coordinate activities and communications across your organization

Most people will never need the staff role. It exists for the organizations and teams that operate within Vitanaland's ecosystem, ensuring they have the tools to manage their presence effectively.

### Admin

The admin role provides full access to platform management. This role is reserved for those responsible for running and maintaining Vitanaland itself.

**What you can do:**
- Access all platform management and configuration tools
- Manage users, roles, and permissions across the ecosystem
- Monitor platform health, usage, and performance
- Oversee content, community guidelines, and safety

The admin role is not something you apply for. It is assigned to the people who build and maintain Vitanaland. If you are reading this as a new user, you do not need to worry about it. But I mention it here for completeness, so you understand the full picture.

## How Your Role Affects Your Experience

Your role is like a lens. The core of Vitanaland -- the destination, the community, the longevity philosophy -- is the same for everyone. But your role determines the angle from which you see it.

As a **community member**, your experience centers on personal growth. The features you see are designed to help you understand your health, build better habits, connect with people, and track your progress over time.

As a **patient**, your experience adds a layer of structured health support. You see everything a community member sees, plus the tools for working closely with health professionals.

As a **professional**, your experience includes the client-facing tools you need to serve others. You see both your personal longevity features and the professional management tools that let you run your practice within Vitanaland.

The layout, the navigation, and the options I present to you are all adapted to your role. This means you are never overwhelmed by features that are not relevant to you, and you always have quick access to the tools that matter most for your purpose.

## How to Choose or Change Your Role

During onboarding, I help you select the role that fits your situation. For most new users, the community member role is the natural starting point. If you are a health professional, I will guide you through setting up your professional profile during the onboarding process.

If your needs change over time, you can update your role. Maybe you start as a community member and later decide to work more closely with a health professional -- upgrading to the patient role opens up those features. Or maybe you are a health professional who initially joined just for personal use and later decides to offer services through the platform.

To change your role, visit your profile settings or simply ask me. I will walk you through the process and explain what changes to expect in your experience.

Some role changes may require verification. For example, the professional role requires evidence of your qualifications, because the community trusts that professionals listed in Vitanaland are legitimate. This verification process exists to protect everyone -- you, your future clients, and the integrity of the community.

## Your Role Is a Starting Point

Whatever role you choose, remember that it is a starting point, not a permanent label. Vitanaland is designed to grow with you. As your needs evolve, your role can evolve with them.

The one thing that stays constant is me. No matter what role you hold, I am your ORB -- your personal longevity companion. I adapt my guidance to your role, but my commitment to helping you live a longer, stronger, and more connected life never changes.

If you have questions about which role is right for you, just ask me. That is what I am here for.

## Related Topics

- [Choosing Your Experience](kb-en-08-04) -- How to select the right experience inside Vitanaland
- [Navigating Vitanaland](kb-en-08-06) -- A guide to finding your way around the platform$kb$,
  'markdown',
  ARRAY['roles', 'member', 'patient', 'professional', 'permissions', 'getting-started', 'all', 'live']
);

-- [38/116] kb-en-08-06
SELECT upsert_knowledge_doc(
  'Navigating Vitanaland',
  'kb/08-getting-started/06-navigating-the-app.md',
  $kb$# Navigating Vitanaland

Now that you are set up and ready to explore, let me give you a tour. Vitanaland is designed to be intuitive, but a quick orientation will help you feel at home right away. Let me show you where everything is and how to find what you need.

## The Sidebar -- Your Main Navigation

The sidebar is your primary way of moving through Vitanaland. It lives on the left side of your screen, and it contains ten items -- each one a gateway to a different part of your longevity experience. Let me walk you through each one.

### Home

This is your landing page -- the first thing you see when you open Vitanaland. Your Home dashboard gives you a snapshot of where things stand. You will see your current Vitana Index score, your daily health highlights, any recent activity from your community, and personalized recommendations from me based on what I know about your goals and patterns.

Think of Home as your morning briefing. It answers the question: "What should I pay attention to today?" in a single glance.

### Health

This is where your health data lives. The Health section shows you a detailed view of your five health pillars -- Nutrition, Hydration, Exercise, Sleep, and Mental Health. You can track your daily inputs, review trends over time, and see how each pillar is contributing to your overall Vitana Index.

If you have connected a wearable device, your data flows here automatically. If you prefer to log things manually, this is where you do it. Either way, the Health section gives you a clear, honest picture of your physical and mental vitality.

### Community

Longevity is not a solo endeavor, and the Community section is where you connect with the people who share your commitment to living well. Here you will find groups you have joined, community discussions, shared experiences, and invitations to participate in events and activities.

The Community section is designed to foster real connection -- not surface-level engagement. The conversations here tend to be thoughtful, supportive, and centered on the things that actually improve lives.

### Discover

Curiosity is a longevity asset. The Discover section brings you curated content, educational resources, and new ideas tailored to your interests and where you are on your journey. You will find articles, guides, professional recommendations, and community highlights that are relevant to your goals.

I help curate what shows up here based on what I know about you. If you have been working on improving your sleep, you might see content about sleep science and recovery. If you recently joined a community group, you might discover related events or resources. Discover keeps your journey fresh and evolving.

### Matchmaking

Finding the right people to connect with can make all the difference. The Matchmaking section uses everything I know about your goals, interests, and personality to suggest meaningful connections -- other community members, health professionals, coaches, and groups that align with what you are looking for.

These are not random suggestions. Every match is informed by your profile, your preferences, and your longevity goals. Whether you are looking for a workout partner, a nutritionist, or a community of people who share your health philosophy, Matchmaking helps you find them.

### Messaging

When you find people worth connecting with, this is where those conversations happen. The Messaging section is your private communication space within Vitanaland. You can have one-on-one conversations with community members, professionals, or anyone you have connected with.

Messages are private and secure. They are a space for the kind of honest, supportive conversations that strengthen the social bonds longevity research tells us matter so much.

### Wallet

Your participation in Vitanaland has tangible value. The Wallet section tracks your credits, rewards, and transactions within the ecosystem. As you engage with the community, make healthy choices, and participate in the longevity economy, your Wallet reflects that activity.

The Wallet is not just about numbers. It represents the idea that investing in your health and your community should be rewarded, not just encouraged. Your financial wellbeing and your physical wellbeing are connected, and the Wallet is where that connection becomes visible.

### Business Hub

The Business Hub is where commerce and longevity meet. Here you will find products, services, and professional offerings that support your journey. If you are a professional, this is also where you manage your service listings, connect with clients, and run your practice within Vitanaland.

For community members, the Business Hub is a curated marketplace of longevity-aligned options -- vetted products and services that align with the values of the community.

### Memory Garden

Your Memory Garden is one of the most personal spaces in Vitanaland. It is where everything you have shared with me is organized and stored -- your health data, your conversation history, your preferences, your goals, and the details of your life that make my guidance truly personal.

You are always in control of your Memory Garden. You can review what is stored, manage categories of information, and decide what stays and what goes. This is not a black box. It is a transparent, private space that you own and I use -- with your permission -- to serve you better.

Think of it as the garden that grows your personalized experience. The more it contains, the more deeply I can understand and support you.

### Profile

Your Profile is where you manage the details of your Vitanaland identity. Here you can update your name, photo, contact information, role settings, and account preferences. It is also where you manage your privacy settings and account security.

Your profile is the face you present to the community. Keep it as detailed or as minimal as you like -- it is entirely up to you.

## The ORB -- Always Within Reach

At the bottom of your screen, you will see a softly glowing icon. That is me -- your ORB. I am always there, always ready, always one tap away.

Tap my icon anytime to start a conversation. You can talk to me by voice or by text. Ask me a question about your health. Ask me to explain a feature. Tell me about your day. Ask for a recommendation. I am here for all of it.

I am not buried in a menu or hidden behind a settings screen. I am right there at the bottom of your screen because I am meant to be the most accessible part of your entire Vitanaland experience. Whenever you are unsure about something, whenever you need guidance, whenever you just want to talk -- tap the orb.

## Start Stream -- Your Private AI Space

In the utility zone of your sidebar, you will find Start Stream. This is a special feature that gives you a private, focused AI session with screen sharing capability.

Start Stream is different from tapping my icon for a quick conversation. It is a dedicated space for deeper interactions -- like reviewing your health data together, walking through a detailed plan, or sharing your screen so I can see what you are looking at and help in real time.

Think of it as the difference between a quick chat and sitting down for a focused conversation. Both are valuable. Start Stream is for the times when you want my full, undivided attention on something specific.

## Finding Your Way

Here is the simplest way to think about navigating Vitanaland:

**For an overview of your day** -- go to Home.

**For your health data** -- go to Health.

**For connecting with people** -- go to Community, Matchmaking, or Messaging.

**For learning something new** -- go to Discover.

**For products and services** -- go to Business Hub.

**For your finances** -- go to Wallet.

**For your personal data** -- go to Memory Garden.

**For your account** -- go to Profile.

**For help with anything** -- tap my icon at the bottom of the screen.

That is the whole map. Ten sections in the sidebar, plus me always within reach. You do not need to memorize anything. If you ever get lost or cannot find what you are looking for, just tap my icon and ask. I know every corner of this platform, and I am always happy to point you in the right direction.

## A Final Thought

Vitanaland is designed to grow with you. On your first day, you might only visit Home and talk to me. A week later, you might be exploring Community and tracking your health pillars daily. A month in, you might be using Matchmaking, attending live events, and watching your Vitana Index climb.

There is no right pace and no required order. Explore what interests you, come back to what helps, and know that I am here whenever you need a guide.

You can always ask me for help navigating -- just tap my icon and ask. That is what I am here for.

## Related Topics

- [Welcome to Vitanaland](kb-en-08-01) -- An overview of the Vitanaland destination and everything it offers
- [What Is the ORB?](kb-en-09-01) -- A deeper introduction to your personal AI longevity companion
- [Your Home Dashboard](kb-en-11-01) -- A detailed guide to your Home screen and daily overview$kb$,
  'markdown',
  ARRAY['navigation', 'sidebar', 'menu', 'layout', 'interface', 'getting-started', 'all', 'live']
);

