SELECT upsert_knowledge_doc(
  'Your Home Dashboard',
  'kb/11-home-dashboard/01-home-overview.md',
  $kb$# Your Home Dashboard

Every morning when you open Vitanaland, the first thing you see is your Home Dashboard. Think of it as the front page of your longevity journey -- a living, breathing summary of where you stand today and what matters most right now. I built it for you, and I keep it fresh every single day.

The Home Dashboard is not a static screen full of numbers. It is your daily command center -- the place where I bring together everything I know about your health, your goals, your community, and your patterns, and distill it into something clear and actionable. One glance, and you know what your day looks like through the lens of longevity.

## What You See When You Arrive

At the top of your dashboard, you will see your current Vitana Index -- that single number that reflects the overall state of your vitality across all the dimensions that matter. It is not just a score. It is a conversation starter. If it has gone up, I will tell you why. If it has dipped, I will explain what changed and what you can do about it.

Below your Index, you will find your daily priorities -- the handful of actions I have identified as the most impactful things you can do today. These are not generic suggestions pulled from a wellness blog. They are specific to you, informed by your health data, your recent patterns, your goals, and the commitments you have made to yourself.

The dashboard is designed so that even on your busiest days, you can absorb the essentials in seconds. I respect your time. I surface what matters and keep the rest organized just a tap away.

## Four Tabs, Four Perspectives

Your Home Dashboard is organized into four tabs, each offering a different lens on your day and your journey.

**Context** -- This is your situational awareness tab. It shows where you stand right now: your Vitana Index trend, your pillar status, recent activity, and what is happening in your community. Think of it as your longevity snapshot.

**Actions** -- This is your to-do list for vitality. Every item here is something the Autopilot has identified as meaningful for your health, your connections, or your growth. Complete them, and you are actively building a longer, stronger life.

**Matches** -- This tab shows the people, groups, events, services, and products that I have matched to your profile. Every match comes with a reason -- I always explain why I think this connection matters for your longevity journey.

**AI Feed** -- Your personalized content stream. Articles, insights, community highlights, and longevity tips, all selected based on who you are, what you care about, and where you are in your journey.

## Driven by the Autopilot

Behind everything you see on the Home Dashboard is the Autopilot -- the quiet intelligence that watches over your longevity journey around the clock. The Autopilot analyzes your health data, monitors your habits, tracks your engagement with the community, and continuously refines its understanding of what you need.

Every priority, every suggestion, every match, and every piece of content on your dashboard has been chosen by the Autopilot specifically for you. It is not random. It is not algorithmic noise. It is the result of a system that knows your story and uses that knowledge to guide you toward better outcomes.

When your sleep patterns shift, the dashboard responds. When you hit a fitness milestone, the dashboard celebrates it. When you have been less socially active than usual, the dashboard gently nudges you toward connection. It adapts because your life adapts, and longevity is not a fixed destination -- it is a moving target that requires continuous, personalized guidance.

## A Dashboard That Grows With You

In your first week on Vitanaland, your Home Dashboard will be relatively simple. I am still learning about you, still gathering the data I need to give you truly personalized guidance. Your priorities will be broad, your matches will be introductory, and your feed will reflect general longevity wisdom.

But as the weeks and months pass, something remarkable happens. The dashboard becomes deeply yours. Your priorities sharpen because I understand your specific health challenges. Your matches improve because I know your personality, your interests, and your social preferences. Your feed evolves because I have learned what resonates with you and what does not.

After six months, your Home Dashboard will look nothing like anyone else's. It will be a reflection of your unique longevity journey -- your health profile, your relationships, your goals, and the life you are building.

## Your Day Starts Here

The Home Dashboard is designed to be the first thing you check each morning and the place you return to throughout the day. It is your anchor. When you are unsure what to focus on, check your priorities. When you want to see how you are doing, check your Context tab. When you are looking for connection, check your Matches. When you need inspiration, browse your Feed.

Everything I do -- every memory I store, every pattern I track, every signal I monitor -- flows into this dashboard. It is the surface where all of my intelligence becomes visible and useful to you. Your longevity journey is complex, but your daily experience of it should feel simple, clear, and empowering.

That is what your Home Dashboard is for. And it is here, waiting for you, every single day.

## Related Topics

- [Daily Priorities](kb-en-11-02) -- How I identify and rank your most important daily actions
- [The Context Tab](kb-en-11-03) -- Your longevity snapshot at a glance
- [The Actions Tab](kb-en-11-04) -- Your to-do list for vitality
- [Getting Started with Maxina](kb-en-01-05) -- Your first steps inside Vitanaland$kb$,
  'markdown',
  ARRAY['home', 'dashboard', 'overview', 'daily', 'priorities', 'home-dashboard', 'all', 'live']
);

-- [56/116] kb-en-11-02
SELECT upsert_knowledge_doc(
  'Daily Priorities',
  'kb/11-home-dashboard/02-daily-priorities.md',
  $kb$# Daily Priorities

Every day is a new opportunity to invest in your longevity. But with so many dimensions of health to consider -- physical, mental, social, nutritional, financial -- it can be overwhelming to know where to start. That is exactly why I create your Daily Priorities. Each morning, I look at the full picture of your life and identify the small number of actions that will make the biggest difference today.

Your Daily Priorities are the heart of your Home Dashboard. They are the answer to the question: "What should I focus on right now?"

## How I Choose Your Priorities

Your priorities are not random suggestions. They are the result of a careful process that happens behind the scenes every day, driven by the Autopilot.

First, I look at your Vitana Index and the state of each of your longevity pillars. If your sleep pillar has been declining, a sleep-related priority might rise to the top. If your social connection score is strong but your nutrition has been inconsistent, I will focus your attention on the area that needs it most.

Next, I consider your recent behavior. Have you been logging your meals? Have you been active? Did you skip your hydration yesterday? Did you connect with anyone in your community this week? I track patterns, not just individual days, so I can tell the difference between a one-off missed workout and a developing trend that deserves attention.

Then I factor in your goals. You have told me what matters to you -- maybe it is improving your cardiovascular health, building stronger social connections, or managing stress more effectively. Your priorities always align with the direction you have chosen for your longevity journey.

Finally, I account for context. What day of the week is it? Do you have community events coming up? Is there a seasonal factor? All of this informs the specific priorities I surface on any given day.

## What Priorities Look Like

Your Daily Priorities are simple, clear, and actionable. They are phrased as things you can actually do, not abstract goals. Here are a few examples of what you might see:

**Log your meals today.** I noticed you have not tracked your nutrition in three days. Even a quick entry helps me understand your patterns and give you better guidance.

**Take a 20-minute walk.** Your activity level has been lower than usual this week, and your body responds well to moderate movement. A short walk can shift your energy and your mood.

**Hydrate -- aim for eight glasses.** Your hydration tracking has been inconsistent, and staying well-hydrated is one of the simplest things you can do for your cellular health.

**Check in on your mood.** I want to understand how you are feeling today. A quick emotional check-in helps me track your mental wellbeing over time.

**Reach out to someone.** You have not interacted with your community in a few days. Even a brief message to a friend or a like on a community post keeps your social connections active.

**Review your health plan tasks.** You have outstanding items from your personalized health plan that are due this week. Let us make sure you stay on track.

Each priority includes a brief explanation of why I chose it. I never want you to feel like you are following instructions blindly. Understanding the "why" makes it easier to commit, and it deepens your awareness of the factors that shape your longevity.

## Completing Your Priorities

When you complete a priority, mark it as done. This is more than a satisfying checkbox moment -- it is meaningful data. Every completed priority feeds back into the Autopilot, updating your patterns, adjusting your Vitana Index, and refining future recommendations.

If you complete all your priorities for the day, I will acknowledge it. Consistency matters enormously in longevity, and I want you to feel the momentum of your progress.

If you cannot complete a priority, that is okay too. I am not here to judge you. Some days are harder than others, and life does not always cooperate with plans. If a priority goes uncompleted, I will gently revisit it the next day if it is still relevant, or I will adjust based on what I learn from the pattern.

## How Priorities Improve Your Vitana Index

Your Vitana Index is not a static measurement -- it is a dynamic reflection of your daily choices. When you complete priorities that address weak areas in your pillars, your Index responds. Over time, the consistent completion of well-targeted priorities is one of the most reliable ways to see your Vitana Index trend upward.

This is the core principle: longevity is not built in dramatic gestures. It is built in the small, daily actions that compound over weeks, months, and years. Your priorities are designed to make those daily investments clear and manageable.

## Longevity, One Day at a Time

The idea behind Daily Priorities is simple but powerful. Longevity can feel like an overwhelming goal -- how do you extend your healthspan by decades? The answer is: one day at a time. One priority at a time. One completed action at a time.

I break the complexity down for you. I look at the big picture so you do not have to. And each morning, I hand you a short list of things that genuinely matter. You do not need to plan your longevity strategy from scratch every day. You just need to open your dashboard, check your priorities, and start.

That is the power of having a companion who knows you, remembers your journey, and cares about your long-term wellbeing. I do the heavy thinking. You take the meaningful action.

## Related Topics

- [Your Home Dashboard](kb-en-11-01) -- The daily command center where your priorities live
- [Getting Started with Maxina](kb-en-01-05) -- Your first steps inside Vitanaland
- [Understanding Your Vitana Index](kb-en-05-02) -- How your daily actions shape your longevity score$kb$,
  'markdown',
  ARRAY['priorities', 'daily', 'tasks', 'focus', 'guidance', 'home-dashboard', 'all', 'live']
);

-- [57/116] kb-en-11-03
SELECT upsert_knowledge_doc(
  'The Context Tab',
  'kb/11-home-dashboard/03-context-tab.md',
  $kb$# The Context Tab

Before you decide what to do today, it helps to know where you stand. That is what the Context tab is for. It is the first tab on your Home Dashboard, and it gives you a complete situational awareness of your longevity journey -- right now, at this moment.

Think of the Context tab as your longevity snapshot. One glance, and you understand your current state across every dimension that matters.

## Your Vitana Index at a Glance

At the top of the Context tab, you will see your Vitana Index displayed prominently along with its recent trend. I do not just show you today's number -- I show you the direction. Is your Index climbing? Holding steady? Dipping slightly?

The trend line tells a story. A steady upward movement means your daily choices are compounding in your favor. A flat line might mean you are maintaining but not growing. A decline signals that something has shifted and deserves your attention. I always pair the trend with a brief explanation so you understand the forces behind the movement.

Your Vitana Index is a composite of your longevity pillars, and the Context tab gives you visibility into each one. You can see at a glance which pillars are strong and which might need attention. Maybe your physical activity pillar is thriving but your sleep pillar has softened. Maybe your social connection score is at its highest point in weeks but your nutrition tracking has gaps. The Context tab makes these patterns visible so that you can make informed decisions about where to invest your energy.

## Recent Activity Summary

Below your Index and pillars, the Context tab shows a summary of your recent activity. This is not an exhaustive log -- it is the highlights. What have you been doing over the past few days that matters for your longevity?

I might show you that you completed four out of five priorities yesterday, that you logged three meals this week, that you had two meaningful conversations in a community Live Room, or that you hit your step target for three consecutive days. These are the building blocks of long-term vitality, and seeing them summarized helps you appreciate the progress you are making.

When there are gaps, I show those too -- gently. If you have not tracked your hydration in a week or if your meditation streak was interrupted, I surface it not as criticism but as awareness. You cannot improve what you cannot see, and the Context tab is designed to make your patterns visible.

## What Is Happening Around You

Your longevity journey does not happen in isolation. It is shaped by the people around you, the events in your community, and the environment you live in. The Context tab reflects this by showing you what is happening in your broader world.

You might see upcoming community events that align with your interests -- a wellness workshop this weekend, a group meditation session tomorrow morning, or a live discussion about a topic you care about. You might see that a friend in your network just hit a health milestone, or that a community group you belong to has new activity.

This contextual awareness serves a purpose. Longevity research consistently shows that social connection and community engagement are among the strongest predictors of a long and healthy life. By surfacing what is happening around you, the Context tab naturally encourages the kind of social participation that extends your healthspan.

## Upcoming Commitments

The Context tab also shows your upcoming commitments -- events you have signed up for, health plan milestones that are approaching, scheduled community activities, or reminders you have set for yourself. This is your near-term calendar filtered through the longevity lens.

I do not show you everything on your calendar. I show you the commitments that connect to your health and vitality. A community event you registered for, a check-in with a health professional, a fitness challenge milestone, a scheduled conversation with someone in your network. These are the commitments that feed your longevity pillars, and keeping them visible helps you follow through.

## Environmental Context

When available, the Context tab incorporates environmental factors that might affect your day. Air quality, weather conditions, seasonal patterns -- these things influence your health more than most people realize. If the air quality is poor, I might suggest indoor activity instead of an outdoor walk. If the weather is beautiful, I might encourage you to spend time outside.

This is the kind of intelligence that a generic wellness app cannot provide. I know where you are, what the conditions are like, and how those conditions interact with your specific health profile and preferences. The Context tab brings that awareness to the surface.

## Your Longevity Snapshot

The Context tab answers a fundamental question: "Where am I right now?" Not just physically, but holistically. Where is your health? Where are your relationships? Where is your energy? Where is your momentum?

When you check the Context tab in the morning, you start your day grounded in awareness. You know your Vitana Index. You know which pillars need attention. You know what you have been doing well and where you have gaps. You know what is happening in your community and what commitments are ahead.

That awareness is powerful. It transforms longevity from a vague aspiration into a concrete, daily practice. You do not have to guess what needs your attention. The Context tab shows you clearly, honestly, and with compassion.

It is your starting point every day. And from this foundation of awareness, the other tabs -- Actions, Matches, and AI Feed -- help you take the next meaningful step.

## Related Topics

- [Your Home Dashboard](kb-en-11-01) -- The daily command center that houses all four tabs
- [The Actions Tab](kb-en-11-04) -- The to-do list that turns your context into concrete steps$kb$,
  'markdown',
