SELECT upsert_knowledge_doc(
  'How Matching Works',
  'kb/15-matchmaking/01-how-matching-works.md',
  $kb$# How Matching Works

One of the most important things I do for you inside Vitanaland is help you find the right people, the right groups, the right events, and the right resources for your longevity journey. I do not leave this to chance. Every match I suggest is the result of a careful process that considers who you are, where you are on your health journey, and what kind of connections will genuinely move your life forward.

Let me walk you through how the matching system works from the inside.

## Longevity-Aligned, Not Surface-Level

Most platforms match people based on what they look like, what music they listen to, or what they happened to click on recently. That approach can produce entertaining results, but it does not produce meaningful ones -- at least not consistently.

I take a fundamentally different approach. Every match I make is longevity-aligned. That means I am looking for connections that support your healthspan, your vitality, and your long-term wellbeing. I care about whether a match will help you build better habits, strengthen your social bonds, fill a gap in your knowledge, or introduce you to a resource that addresses a real need in your life.

This does not mean every match is serious or clinical. Many of the best longevity connections start with something simple -- a shared love of morning walks, a mutual curiosity about cold exposure, or the fact that you both live in the same neighborhood and care about eating well. But even the lightest connections are grounded in something that matters for your health.

## What the Algorithm Considers

The matching system draws on multiple layers of information about you, and it weighs them thoughtfully.

**Your Vitana Index.** Your overall vitality score gives me a broad picture of where you are. But more importantly, the breakdown across your health pillars -- nutrition, hydration, exercise, sleep, and mental health -- tells me where you are strong and where you might benefit from support or inspiration. I use this to find matches that complement your profile.

**Your health goals.** The goals you have set inside Vitanaland carry real weight in the matching process. If you are working on improving your sleep quality, I look for people who have made progress in that area, professionals who specialize in sleep health, or groups focused on recovery and rest. Your goals shape who I introduce you to.

**Your lifestyle patterns.** How you live your daily life matters. Your exercise routines, your eating habits, your sleep schedule, your social activity -- these patterns help me understand what kind of connections will fit naturally into your world. I look for alignment in daily rhythms because shared habits make relationships easier to build and sustain.

**Your community activity.** If you are active in certain groups, attend specific types of events, or engage with particular topics, I factor that in. Your community behavior tells me what genuinely interests you, not just what you say interests you.

**Your preferences.** You can set explicit preferences for the kinds of matches you want -- geographic range, age range, health focus areas, match types, and more. These preferences act as guardrails that I always respect.

**Geographic proximity.** In-person connection carries longevity benefits that digital interaction alone cannot fully replicate. Sharing a meal, walking together, attending a live session in the same room -- these experiences deepen bonds. When someone near you is also a strong longevity match, I make sure you know about it.

**Complementary strengths.** Some of the most valuable connections are not with people who mirror you, but with people who are strong where you are still growing. If your nutrition is solid but your exercise has been inconsistent, I might connect you with someone whose movement practice is deeply established. You each bring something to the relationship.

## Match Score: 0 to 100

Every match I suggest comes with a score from 0 to 100. This is not a grade or a rating of anyone's worth. It is a measure of longevity alignment -- how well this particular match supports your specific health journey at this moment in time.

A score of 85 does not mean the connection is objectively better than one scored at 70. It means the alignment between your profiles, goals, and circumstances is particularly strong right now. Scores shift over time as both you and the other party evolve. A match that scores moderately today might become highly relevant next month as your goals change or as you both progress on your journeys.

I always show you why a match received its score. Transparency matters. You should never have to guess why I am suggesting someone or something.

## Seven Types of Matches

The matching system does not only connect you with people. I match you across seven distinct categories, because your longevity journey needs more than just social connection.

**Person.** Individual connections -- longevity companions, accountability partners, mentors, or simply people whose health values align with yours. These are the most personal matches, and often the most impactful over time.

**Group.** Communities and groups aligned with your interests and goals. A running group, a meditation circle, a nutrition-focused discussion community -- groups give you a sense of belonging and consistent social touchpoints.

**Event.** Upcoming events, workshops, meetups, and sessions that align with your health focus areas. Events turn passive interest into active participation, and attending them strengthens both your knowledge and your social bonds.

**Service.** Health professionals and wellness services tailored to your current needs. A nutritionist, a sleep specialist, a fitness coach, a therapist -- matched based on your specific health profile and pillar gaps.

**Product.** Longevity-aligned products -- supplements, wellness tools, recovery devices -- that address genuine needs in your health journey. These are never random. They are always connected to something specific in your profile.

**Location.** Wellness-friendly places near you -- parks, gyms, wellness centers, healthy restaurants, retreat spaces -- that support your daily routines and long-term habits.

**Live Room.** Active live sessions happening right now or scheduled for the near future. Live rooms are real-time community experiences where you connect with others around shared topics, guided by live hosts. I match you with rooms that align with your interests and health focus.

Each of these match types plays a role in building the full architecture of a long and vibrant life. People, places, events, groups, services, products, and experiences -- they all contribute.

## How Matching Improves Over Time

The matching system is not static. It learns from you continuously.

Every match you accept, every one you dismiss, every connection you deepen, and every one that fades -- all of it teaches me something about what resonates with you. Over days and weeks, the matches I suggest become increasingly tailored to the kind of connections that genuinely enrich your life.

I also learn from your broader behavior. The topics you discuss in conversations, the groups you are most active in, the events you attend, the products you explore -- these patterns refine my understanding of who you are and what you need. You do not have to manually configure everything. The system adapts as you live your life inside Vitanaland.

## Why This Matters

Longevity research is clear: the people and resources around you shape how long and how well you live. Strong social bonds reduce inflammation, lower cortisol, improve immune function, and protect cognitive health. Access to the right professionals and tools can prevent problems before they start. Participating in community events gives you purpose and belonging -- both of which are powerful longevity factors.

I do not match you randomly. I match you with intention, grounded in what the science tells us actually matters for a longer, healthier life. Every suggestion I make is designed to strengthen the ecosystem around you -- the people, places, experiences, and resources that help you thrive.

You do not have to build that ecosystem alone. That is what I am here for.

## Related Topics

- [Intelligent Matchmaking for Longevity](kb-en-04-02) -- The science and philosophy behind longevity-aligned matching
- [Your Daily Matches](kb-en-15-02) -- How fresh matches are delivered to you every day
- [Types of Matches](kb-en-15-03) -- A closer look at all seven match categories$kb$,
  'markdown',
  ARRAY['matchmaking', 'algorithm', 'compatibility', 'longevity', 'connections', 'all', 'live']
);

-- [86/116] kb-en-15-02
SELECT upsert_knowledge_doc(
  'Your Daily Matches',
  'kb/15-matchmaking/02-daily-matches.md',
  $kb$# Your Daily Matches

Every morning, I prepare a fresh set of matches just for you. Think of it as your daily longevity menu -- a curated selection of people, groups, events, services, and resources that I believe can make a meaningful difference in your health journey right now.

These are not random suggestions pulled from a database. Each one is the result of careful alignment between your profile, your goals, your recent activity, and the evolving state of the Vitanaland community around you.

## How Daily Matches Are Generated

The process starts before you even open the app. Overnight, the matching system reviews your current health data, your Vitana Index trends, your recent community activity, your stated goals, and your match preferences. It also considers what has changed in the community -- new members who align with your profile, upcoming events in your area, groups that have gained momentum around topics you care about, and products or services that address your specific pillar gaps.

From all of this, I assemble a set of matches that reflect what matters most for you today. If your sleep quality has been declining, you might see more matches related to sleep -- a recovery-focused group, a sleep health professional, or a community member who has made real progress in that area. If you have been physically active but socially quiet, I might emphasize connections and events that bring you into community.

The algorithm is not mechanical. It is responsive. Your matches evolve as you evolve.

## Where to Find Your Daily Matches

You can access your daily matches in two places.

**Home Dashboard -- Matches Tab.** When you open your home screen, look for the Matches tab. This is the quickest way to see what I have prepared for you today. The matches appear as cards, each one showing the key information you need to decide whether to engage.

**Dedicated Matchmaking Section.** For a fuller experience, navigate to the Matchmaking section. Here you will find your complete daily match set, along with tools to filter, sort, and explore. You can also review past matches, revisit saved suggestions, and adjust your preferences.

Both locations show the same matches -- the dashboard gives you a quick overview, and the dedicated section gives you the full picture.

## Understanding Match Cards

Each match is presented as a card with the information you need at a glance.

**Match type.** An icon or label tells you whether this is a person, group, event, service, product, location, or live room. You can immediately see what kind of connection I am suggesting.

**Match score.** The alignment score from 0 to 100, showing how well this match fits your current profile and goals.

**Key details.** For a person match, you will see their name, a brief bio, and shared interests. For a group, you will see the group name, topic, and member count. For an event, you will see the title, date, and format. Each match type surfaces the details most relevant to that category.

**Why this match.** Every card includes a brief explanation of why I selected this match for you -- the specific factors that make it relevant. This is one of the most important parts of the card. I never ask you to guess why I am introducing something. I tell you directly.

**Actions.** Each card gives you clear options: accept, dismiss, or save for later. One tap is all it takes to act.

## How Many Matches Per Day

The number of daily matches varies depending on what the system finds for you. On a typical day, you might see anywhere from five to fifteen matches across the different types. I never flood you with options just for the sake of volume. If the quality is not there, I would rather show you fewer matches that are genuinely relevant than a long list of mediocre ones.

Some days you might see more person matches if there are strong new alignments. Other days, an event or group might take center stage because something particularly relevant is happening in your area or health focus. The mix changes naturally based on what is most useful for you right now.

## Why Matches Change Daily

Your daily matches are not a static list. They change every day, and that is by design. Here is why.

**You are changing.** Your health data updates, your goals shift, your community engagement evolves, and your Vitana Index reflects new patterns. The matches I showed you yesterday were based on yesterday's version of you. Today's matches reflect today.

**The community is changing.** New people join Vitanaland every day. Existing members update their profiles, create new groups, and schedule new events. The landscape of potential connections is always in motion. Your daily matches capture the most relevant opportunities in that moving landscape.

**Your feedback matters.** Every time you accept, dismiss, or save a match, you teach me something. Yesterday's feedback shapes today's suggestions. The system continuously refines its understanding of what kind of connections resonate with you and adjusts accordingly.

**Timeliness is important.** Some matches are time-sensitive. An event happening this weekend, a live room scheduled for tonight, a professional offering limited availability -- these opportunities have a window. I surface them when they are actionable, not after the moment has passed.

## Building a Habit Around Daily Matches

I encourage you to make checking your daily matches part of your morning routine, just like checking your health dashboard or reviewing your daily priorities. It takes only a few minutes, and over time, the connections you build from these matches become one of the most valuable parts of your longevity journey.

Social connection is not something that happens accidentally for most people. It requires small, consistent actions -- accepting a match, joining a group, attending an event, sending a first message. Your daily matches are designed to make those actions easy and natural, so that building your longevity network feels effortless rather than forced.

Every match is an invitation. You choose which ones to accept. But I promise you, the ones that stick -- the connections that grow into real relationships, the groups that become part of your weekly rhythm, the events that inspire you -- those are the ones that quietly extend your life.

## Related Topics

- [How Matching Works](kb-en-15-01) -- The full explanation of the matching algorithm and what it considers
- [Accepting and Dismissing Matches](kb-en-15-04) -- How to act on your daily matches and how your choices shape future suggestions
- [Home Dashboard Overview](kb-en-11-05) -- Where daily matches appear on your home screen$kb$,
  'markdown',
  ARRAY['daily', 'matches', 'suggestions', 'connections', 'matchmaking', 'all', 'live']
);

-- [87/116] kb-en-15-03
SELECT upsert_knowledge_doc(
  'Types of Matches',
  'kb/15-matchmaking/03-match-types.md',
  $kb$# Types of Matches

When I suggest a match for you, it is not always a person. Your longevity journey is supported by many kinds of connections -- people, communities, events, professionals, products, places, and real-time experiences. I match you across seven distinct categories, each one designed to fill a different role in building a longer, healthier, and more connected life.

Let me explain each type and how it supports your journey.

## Person Matches

Person matches are individual connections -- real people inside Vitanaland whose health values, goals, and lifestyle patterns align with yours. These are the most personal matches I make, and they are often the ones that carry the greatest long-term impact.

When I suggest a person match, I am looking for genuine longevity alignment. Maybe you share similar health goals and could hold each other accountable. Maybe they have made real progress in an area where you are still growing, and their experience could help you. Maybe you live nearby and share daily routines that would make meeting up natural and easy.

Person matches come in several flavors. You might see a longevity peer who is at a similar stage of their health journey. You might see a mentor -- someone further along a path you are walking. You might see a challenge partner who thrives on shared goals and friendly motivation. Each match card explains the specific nature of the connection so you can decide what feels right.

The science behind this is clear: the people closest to you shape your habits, your stress levels, your motivation, and ultimately your healthspan. Every person match I suggest is an opportunity to strengthen that circle.

## Group Matches

Group matches connect you with communities inside Vitanaland that align with your interests and goals. A group might be organized around a wellness topic like intermittent fasting, strength training over fifty, mindfulness for stress management, or anti-inflammatory nutrition. It might be a local community of people in your city who care about living well. It might be a professional network of coaches, nutritionists, or longevity practitioners.

Groups give you something that one-on-one connections alone cannot: a sense of belonging to something larger. Research from the Blue Zones consistently shows that communities where people gather regularly -- sharing meals, moving together, celebrating together -- produce longer, healthier lives. Groups replicate that dynamic inside Vitanaland.

When I match you with a group, I consider the group's focus, its activity level, the health profiles of its members, and how well the group culture fits your personality. I would rather connect you with one active, well-aligned group than a dozen that do not resonate.

## Event Matches

Event matches are about timeliness and opportunity. Workshops, fitness sessions, wellness seminars, community meetups, guided challenges -- these are scheduled experiences that bring people together around shared topics.

I match you with events based on what you care about and what is happening near you or in the digital community. If you have been focused on improving your nutrition, I might suggest an upcoming cooking workshop. If your mental health pillar has been a focus, a stress management seminar might appear. If a community you belong to is hosting a live meetup in your area, I make sure you know about it.

Events matter for longevity because they turn intention into action. It is one thing to say you want to improve your social connections. It is another to show up at an event, meet new people, and share an experience together. That act of showing up -- of physically or virtually participating -- activates the social and neurological systems that protect your health over time.

Event matches include the date, time, format (virtual or in-person), and a clear explanation of why this particular event is relevant to you right now.

## Service Matches

Service matches connect you with health professionals and wellness practitioners who can address specific needs in your longevity journey. Nutritionists, fitness coaches, sleep specialists, therapists, preventive medicine doctors, wellness consultants -- these are people with expertise that can help you make targeted progress.

I do not suggest service matches randomly. They are tied to your health data, your pillar gaps, and your stated goals. If your sleep quality has been declining and your own efforts to improve it have not been enough, I might suggest a sleep specialist. If your exercise routine needs professional guidance, I might surface a coach whose specialization matches your goals.

Every service match includes the professional's credentials, specializations, availability, and a clear explanation of why they are relevant to you. I want you to feel informed and confident before you reach out.

Service matches are important because longevity is not a solo project. There are times when expert guidance can save you months of trial and error, catch a problem early, or unlock a breakthrough that self-directed effort alone cannot achieve.

## Product Matches

Product matches introduce you to longevity-aligned supplements, wellness tools, and health products that address genuine needs in your health profile. Vitamins, minerals, adaptogens, hydration tools, sleep aids, recovery devices, cognitive support supplements -- all carefully vetted and aligned with the Maxina longevity philosophy.

When I suggest a product, it is always connected to something specific. I do not recommend a magnesium supplement just because it is popular. I recommend it because your sleep data suggests a potential benefit, or because your recovery patterns indicate a gap that magnesium has been shown to address. The link between the product and your health is always made explicit.

I want to be clear about something: products complement a healthy lifestyle. They do not replace it. No supplement can substitute for consistent sleep, regular movement, good nutrition, strong social bonds, and emotional wellbeing. Products are one piece of the puzzle, never the whole picture.

## Location Matches

Location matches surface wellness-friendly places near you -- parks, gyms, wellness centers, healthy restaurants, walking trails, yoga studios, retreat spaces, and more. Your physical environment plays a meaningful role in your longevity, and having easy access to places that support healthy living makes it easier to build and sustain good habits.

I match you with locations based on your geographic area, your activity patterns, and your interests. If you walk regularly, I might highlight a scenic trail near your home. If you have been looking for a gym with strength training facilities, I surface options close by. If a new wellness center opens in your area that aligns with your profile, I let you know.

Location matches also support in-person connection. When I know that people in your match network frequent the same gym or park, the opportunity for real-world encounters becomes part of the equation. Some of the strongest longevity bonds start with a shared space.

## Live Room Matches

Live room matches connect you with real-time community sessions happening inside Vitanaland. Live rooms are hosted conversations, workshops, fitness sessions, meditations, or social gatherings where people come together around a shared topic, guided by a host.

I match you with live rooms based on the topic, the host, the other participants, and how the session aligns with your current health focus. If a room focused on sleep optimization is scheduled for tonight and sleep has been your primary goal this month, that match will be prominent. If a live fitness session is happening this weekend with members from your local community, I will surface it.

Live rooms are powerful for longevity because they combine social connection with active engagement. You are not passively reading content. You are participating in a shared experience in real time. That combination of belonging, learning, and interaction is exactly what longevity research tells us makes a difference.

## All Seven Types Working Together

No single match type builds a long life on its own. It is the combination that matters.

A person match introduces you to someone who becomes your walking partner. A group match connects you with a community that holds you accountable. An event match gets you out of the house and into a shared experience. A service match gives you professional guidance for a health challenge you have been struggling with. A product match addresses a nutritional gap. A location match gives you a new place to exercise. A live room match brings everything together in real time.

When these seven types work in concert, they create the full ecosystem of support that longevity requires. That is why I do not just match you with people. I match you with everything your health journey needs.

## Related Topics

- [How Matching Works](kb-en-15-01) -- The algorithm and factors behind every match
- [Intelligent Matchmaking for Longevity](kb-en-04-02) -- The science and philosophy of longevity-aligned matching$kb$,
  'markdown',
  ARRAY['match-types', 'person', 'group', 'event', 'service', 'matchmaking', 'all', 'live']
);

